OpenVisualizer v0.0000001

Directory structure:

base/		basic functionality used in all other components
d3d9drv/	Direct3D 9 video driver
main/		main application code
math/		math codebase
opengldrv/	OpenGL video driver
video/		code for video graphics processing

Needed libraries in linux:
X11
GL
xxf86vm
m
dl

You need one of these packages in debian/ubuntu:
libxxf86vm-dev
xlibs-static-dev

Code in base/, math/, opengldrv/, d3d9drv/ and video/ originated from
the Ion Engine codebase, which is LGPL-licensed. For more info, contact
Carlos Rafael Giani (dv@dword.org).
